article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — Chaz Lanier's 29 points helped North Florida defeat Queens 93-79 on Wednesday night. Lanier also contributed nine rebounds for the Ospreys (14-13, 7-5 Atlantic Sun Conference). Jah Nze scored 22 points while shooting 7 for 13 (3 for 6 from 3-point range) and 5 of 6 from the free throw line. Nate Lliteras had 13 points and was 4 of 5 shooting (3 for 4 from 3-point range). AJ McKee led the way for the Royals (10-17, 4-8) with 30 points, six rebounds, four assists and two steals. Kalib Mathews added 14 points, seven rebounds and two steals for Queens. In addition, BJ McLaurin had eight points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
